title: Sri Bannari Amman
subTitle: Goddess Bannari Amman takes the form of a skilled healer, travelling through small villages to cure people's ailments. On her divine mission, she vanquishes evil and blesses the righteous.

title: Oru Kaidhiyin Diary
subTitle: David, a politically active person, is married to Rosy. However, when his political idol, mistreats his wife, he vows to take revenge.

title: Kannan Varuvaan
subTitle: Kannan wants to continue the construction of a temple left incomplete by his forefathers. However, chaos ensues when he gets forcibly pulled into a crime.

title: Kadal Pookkal
subTitle: Two friends, Karuthaiya and Peter, find their bond tested when a personal tragedy strikes one of their families, leading them on a quest for justice.

title: 49-O
subTitle: When the farmers of a village are tricked into selling their lands to a local politician, a man sympathetic to the plight of farmers decides to get them their properties back.

title: Nadigan
subTitle: Desperate for money, a man poses as an elderly tutor for two young women. Later, he catches feelings for one of them while also wooing their guardian at the same time.

title: Raa Raa
subTitle: Raj Kiran, a filmmaker who is down on his luck, tries to revive his career by shooting a horror movie in a dingy bungalow. However, he and his crew are unaware that the bungalow is actually haunted.

title: Veera Sivaji
subTitle: Sivaji, a taxi driver, strives to raise money for the surgery of his niece. However, chaos ensues, when he gets deceived and strives to overcome the challenges.
